Reasoning: The paper proposes a new acquisition scheme for GPS signals based on the analog compressed sensing framework. This involves a multichannel sampling structure with far fewer correlators, which outputs linear combinations of a vector whose support tends to be sparse. The paper discusses the analysis and implementation of this scheme, as well as its advantages over existing GPS signal acquisition algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Other possible sub-categories include cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SP (Speech and Signal Processing).
